<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[93,620,665,1550]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
COMMENTS: Hartert did not designate a 
<typeStatus box="[93,195,816,838]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
in the original description; by listing Wright’s specimen No. 4 as the type, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert" firstAuthor="Hartert" page="159" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="123 - 178" refId="ref125804" refString="Hartert, E. 1919. Types of birds in the Tring Museum. B. Types in the general collection. Novitates Zoologicae 26: 123 - 178." type="journal article" year="1919">Hartert (1919: 159)</bibRefCitation>
later designated it the 
<typeStatus box="[483,588,875,897]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[93,420,904,927]" class="Aves" family="Passeridae" genus="Passer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="hispaniolensis" subSpecies="maltae">
<emphasis box="[93,420,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Passer hispaniolensis maltae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert" firstAuthor="Hartert" page="332" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="322 - 339" refId="ref125014" refString="Hartert, E. 1902 a. Aus den Wanderjaren eines Naturforschers. IV. Abschnitt. Fruhlongsausflug nach Marokko und Tenerife. II. Kapitel. Mazagan im mittleren Marokko. Novitates Zoologicae 9: 322 - 339." type="journal article" year="1902" yearSuffix="a">Hartert (1902a: 332)</bibRefCitation>
based his description on 
<specimenCount box="[442,537,935,957]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" type="adult">34 adult</specimenCount>
males, 32 of which came to AMNH with the Rothschild Collection. The 
<specimenCount box="[416,619,994,1016]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">31 paralectotypes</specimenCount>
in AMNH are: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[321,612,1023,1044]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">AMNH 718979–718982</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[93,270,1053,1074]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">718985–718993</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[283,461,1053,1074]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">718996–719009</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">719011– 719014</emphasis>
. Six of these bear Jardine labels and five of them have Jardine sale numbers in red on the reverse of the label; these probably came to Rothschild from Edward Bartlett (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert" box="[93,330,1201,1223]" firstAuthor="Hartert" page="159" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="123 - 178" refId="ref125804" refString="Hartert, E. 1919. Types of birds in the Tring Museum. B. Types in the general collection. Novitates Zoologicae 26: 123 - 178." type="journal article" year="1919">Hartert, 1919: 159</bibRefCitation>
). The remainder came directly to Rothschild from the collectors Wright and Adams, who were collecting on 
<collectingCountry box="[93,164,1290,1312]" name="Malta" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Malta</collectingCountry>
in 1860–1861.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[93,620,665,1550]" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
The relationship of the 
<collectingCountry box="[393,464,1321,1343]" name="Malta" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">Malta</collectingCountry>
specimens to 
<emphasis box="[93,363,1350,1373]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[93,251,1350,1373]" class="Aves" family="Passeridae" genus="Passer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="domesticus">P. domesticus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vieillot" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[261,363,1350,1373]" class="Aves" family="Passeridae" genus="Passer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="italiae">P. italiae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1820" box="[426,611,1350,1373]" class="Aves" family="Passeridae" genus="Passer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hispaniolensis">
<emphasis box="[426,611,1350,1373]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">P. hispaniolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and of these species to each other, has been much discussed in the literature. The most recent treatment (
<bibRefCitation author="Summers-Smith" firstAuthor="Summers-Smith" page="794 - 795" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" pagination="793 - 813" refId="ref137909" refString="Summers-Smith, J. D. 2009. Family Passeridae (Old World Sparrows), species accounts. In J. del Hoyo, A. Elliott and D. Christie (editors). Handbook of the birds of the world. Vol. 14, Bush shrikes to Old World sparrows: 793 - 813. Barcelona: Lynx Edicions, 893 pp, 51 pls., photographs." type="book chapter" year="2009">Summers-Smith, 2009: 794– 795</bibRefCitation>
) considered the three to be separate species and 
<emphasis box="[259,336,1498,1521]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">maltae</emphasis>
a hybrid population between 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vieillot" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[196,299,1527,1550]" class="Aves" family="Passeridae" genus="Passer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="italiae">
<emphasis box="[196,299,1527,1550]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">P. italiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[360,577,1527,1550]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="8">
P. h. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1820" box="[423,577,1527,1550]" class="Aves" family="Passeridae" genus="Passer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hispaniolensis">hispaniolensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
